## A list of definitions for a multinational companies, SME companies, and start-up companies

##Multinational Company
A multinational company is a large organisation that operates in more than one country. These companies usually have offices, factories, or branches in different parts of the world and manage their business internationally.

##SME (Small and Medium Enterprise)
An SME is a small or medium-sized business with a limited number of employees and smaller revenue compared to large corporations. SMEs are important for the economy because they create jobs and support local communities.


##Start-up Company
A start-up is a newly created company that is focused on developing an innovative product or service. Start-ups usually aim for rapid growth and often use technology to solve problems in new ways.
